notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Ingest Customer CSV
components.description: Loads raw customer CSV files from the source location and emits file metadata for downstream quality assessment.

connections.purpose: Read raw CSV files from the data lake

components.name: Assess Data Quality
components.description: Calculates a quality score from CSV metadata and decides whether data should be routed to production or quarantine.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful ingestion of CSV metadata

components.name: Load HighQuality Data to Production
components.description: Writes highquality customer data (95% score) into the production database.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered only when quality_check returns the 'production_load' branch

connections.purpose: Write validated customer records to the production database

components.name: Quarantine LowQuality Data
components.description: Moves lowquality customer data (<95% score) to quarantine storage for further inspection.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered only when quality_check returns the 'quarantine_and_alert' branch

connections.purpose: Store lowquality CSV files for later review

components.name: Send Quality Alert Email
components.description: Emails data stewards with details about quality failures when lowquality data is quarantined.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful quarantine of lowquality data

connections.purpose: Send alert email to data stewards

components.name: Final Cleanup
components.description: Deletes temporary files and releases resources after either production load or alert workflow completes.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered after both the production load path and the quarantinealert path have completed

connections.purpose: Remove temporary files created during the pipeline run

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

to.description: Recipient email address for quality alerts

sources: Raw customer CSV files located at /data/raw/
sinks: Production database where highquality customer data is stored
Quarantine storage at /data/quarantine/ for lowquality data
Email notifications sent to data stewards via SMTP
intermediate_datasets: File metadata (path, record count) passed via XCom
Quality score computed for each CSV batch
